DNS Installation and configuration Steps 
Insall bind and bind-utils ÔÉ† yum install bind bind-utils -y 
Enable named service ÔÉ† systemctl enable ‚Äìnow named 
Open configuration file for named ÔÉ† vim /etc/named.conf 
Delete all the existing entries in the file ÔÉ† :%d
Get Inserted in the file and edit ÔÉ†
 options {
	directory ‚Äú/var/named‚Äù;
	recursion no;
zone ‚Äúwordworld.tech‚Äù IN  {
	type master;
	file ‚Äútest‚Äù;
};  
save ÔÉ† :wq!
Check ÔÉ† named-checkconf /etc/named.conf 
Go to data directory ÔÉ† cd /var/named
Copy named.empty file by the name of file you have mentioned in /etc/named.conf ÔÉ† 
cp -p named.empty test
Edit the file ÔÉ† vim test
Change TTL value from 3H to 1M 
Edit file by making records  ÔÉ†
@			IN	NS	ns1.wordworld.tech.
@			IN	NS	ns2.wordworld.tech.
ns1			IN	A	ip of nameserver [same instance you are making entry on now]
ns2			IN	A	ip of nameserver [same instance you are making entry on now]
wordworld.tech.	IN	A	ip of instance you have configured webserver on 
photos			IN	A	ip of instance you have configured webserver on
docs 			IN	A	ip of instance you have configured webserver on
save ÔÉ† :wq!

Restart named service ÔÉ† systemctl restart named 
Change IP in child nameserver and edit new nameserver in nameserver entry of histinger that is ‚Äúns1.wordworld.tech‚Äù and ‚Äúns2.wordworld.tech‚Äù. don‚Äôt forget to remove existing nameserver entries i.e., ‚Äúns1-parking.com‚Äù ‚Äúns2-parking.com‚Äù.
Check ÔÉ† nslookup wordworld.tech localhost 
Allow port 53 in security group of name server 



Steps to configure Webserver [ http ]
install httpd package ÔÉ† yum install httpd -y 
enable httpd sevice ÔÉ† systemctl enable ‚Äìnow httpd 
move to the data directory ÔÉ† cd /var/www/html 
keep content here else make index.html file ÔÉ† vim index.html [ write what you want ]
if want to keep website content !!!
copy link address from ‚Äúfree css template‚Äù and wget it in data directory ÔÉ† wget link 
unzip the zip file you have received ÔÉ† unzip link 
move all the content of unzipped directory outside ÔÉ† mv unzipped-directory/*  .
restart the service ÔÉ† systemctl restart httpd 
allow port 80 on security group of the web server 

Steps to Configure Virtual Hosting 
go to the configuration directory and make files for sub domain ÔÉ† cd /etc/httpd/conf.d
now make files with name of sub domain with extension ‚Äú.conf‚ÄùÔÉ† touch photos.conf  mail.conf  docs.conf 
edit these files individually with their subdomain address and their document roots ÔÉ†
<virtualhost *:80>
servername photos.wordworld.tech
documentroot /var/www/photos
</virtualhost>  
Save :wq!
Now create document directories for each subdomain in /var/www [ e.g mkdir /var/www/photos ]
Check ÔÉ† httpd -t
Steps to allow indexing for virtual hosts 
change in the conf file [ photos.conf ]
<virtualhost *:80>
servername photos.wordworld.tech
documentroot /var/www/photos
</virtualhost>  
<directory /var/www/photos>
options indexes 
</directory> 
Save :wq!



Steps to allow symbolic link for virtual hosting 
<virtualhost *:80>
servername photos.wordworld.tech
documentroot /var/www/photos
</virtualhost>  
<directory /var/www/photos>
options followsymlinks indexes 
</directory> 

Steps to allow file priority in virtual hosting 
<virtualhost *:80>
servername photos.wordworld.tech
documentroot /var/www/photos
</virtualhost>  
<directory /var/www/photos>
options followsymlinks  indexes 
directoryindex  prod.html   test.html   index.html  
</directory> 
[ note : use indexes option with folowsymlinks always ]

Steps to allow or deny specific IP 
<virtualhost *:80>
servername photos.wordworld.tech
